  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Police Professionalization and Community Policing in the Democratic Republic of the Congo - Phase IV</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The goal of Phase IV of this project is to contribute to the improvement of security governance and the rule of law in Lubumbashi, Mbuji Mayi, Goma and Bukavu In the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC) by supporting security sector reform and police professionalization. In light of the evolving security and public health context in the DRC, the project seeks to implement the remaining training activities of the previous phase in addition to expanding the community policing approach and using it to strengthen the police&apos;s COVID-19 response. As such the project will focus on; capacity development of security actors, including police services, civilian authorities, and community members; strengthening of good security governance and the rule of law according to the community policing system and principles; and support to security actors involved in the enforcement of the COVID-19 response plan including any restrictions taken by the Government.</narrative>
  </description>
